[2.0750, "o", "-"]
[2.1000, "o", "h"]
[2.1250, "o", "e"]
[2.1500, "o", "l"]
[2.1750, "o", "p"]
[2.2000, "o", "\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[2.2800, "o", "Age-based secrets management with transport-agnostic sharing\r\n\r\nUsage: himitsu [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>\r\n\r\nCommands:\r\n  init       Initialize himitsu (create keys, config, and optionally a store)\r\n  set        Set a secret value\r\n  get        Get a secret value\r\n  ls         List secrets in the store (or all stores if none resolved)\r\n  rekey      Re-encrypt secrets for current recipients\r\n  sync       Sync stores: pull from git remote and optionally rekey drifted secrets\r\n  search     Search secrets across all known projects\r\n  recipient  Manage recipients\r\n  group      Manage recipient groups\r\n  remote     Manage remote stores (add, remove, list, set default)\r\n  generate   Generate SOPS-encrypted output files from env definitions in project config\r\n  git        Run git commands inside a store checkout (or all stores with --all)\r\n  check      Verify store checkouts are up to date with their remotes\r\n  help       Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)\r\n\r\nOptions:\r\n  -s, --store <STORE>    Override the store path directly (for testing or advanced use)\r\n  -r, --remote <REMOTE>  Select a remote store by org/repo slug (resolves via stores_dir). Mutually exclusive with --store\r\n  -v, --verbose...       Increase log verbosity (-v for debug, -vv for trace)\r\n  -h, --help             Print help\r\n  -V, --version          Print version\r\n"]
[2.3300, "o", "\r\n"]
[3.0300, "o", "\r\n"]
